if (!T13NE) {var T13NE = {};}
window.T13NE.Geometries = [
{"Name":"Void","Geometry":0,"Geometry_Description":"Should never appear.","Chi":"Not Applicable","Yang":"Not Applicable","Yin":"Not Applicable","Goal":"Not Applicable","Goal_Description":"Not Applicable","Gift":"Not Applicable","Gift_Description":"","Suggested_Personality":4,"Harmonic":[1,2,3,4,5,10],"Dissonant":[6,7,8,12,13]},
{"Name":"Circle","Geometry":1,"Geometry_Description":"Circle Characters are determined innovators, creative-thinkers and natural loners and are often perceived as leaders.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by acting confidently, creatively, or alone.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting self-important, domineering or courageous.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting helpless, intolerant, or innovative.","Goal":"Personality","Goal_Description":"Circle characters define their goals from their Personality (or Personalities), usually this is based on their Personalit(y\/ies) Motivation(s) and is usually expressed as a Quest of the same Facet. An Idol character, for example, motivated by a desire to be adored, may make it their personal quest to brave some famous peril, or charm the most people they can (by becoming famous).","Gift":"Determination","Gift_Description":"The Circle Geometry are determined people. They add +1 Success Level on any Action where Determination may help.","Suggested_Personality":4,"Harmonic":[1,3,5,7],"Dissonant":[4,6,12,13]},
{"Name":"Half-Moon","Geometry":2,"Geometry_Description":"Half-Moon Characters are co-operative, harmony seeking diplomats, but they can become manipulative and petty.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by co-operating with others (including following orders), acting diplomatic, or patient.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting sensitive, petty, or detail-orientated.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting intuitive, childish, or supportive.","Goal":"Group","Goal_Description":"Half-moon characters are not dedicated to their own goals, but to the goals of a group or pact. Sometimes they will even dedicate themselves to helping another Character achieve their personal Goals. Half-moon character&#39;s goals will chance and shift as they join and leave groups, and make or lose allies.","Gift":"Harmony","Gift_Description":"The Half-Moon Geometry are sensitive, diplomatic people. They add +1 Success Level on any Action where they are working with others.","Suggested_Personality":13,"Harmonic":[2,4,8,10],"Dissonant":[5,7,11,13]},
{"Name":"Triangle","Geometry":3,"Geometry_Description":"Triangle Characters are intelligent, creative, expressive, often artistic types. They love to talk, being entertaining and all ways have a story to tell, but it may turn gossipy and superficial.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> when you communicate, express yourself, or tell a story.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting optimistic, creatively, intelligently, or by exaggerating.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting emotionally volatile, superficial, insincere, or by sharing gossip.","Goal":"Core","Goal_Description":"Triangle characters are drawn to complete goals based upon their Core(s), usually defined as a Quest that opposes their Core Facet&#39;s Quest. For example, a Wielder Core (Burden) does not themselves have an Obtain Quest, their Goal instead is to protect or guard the Descendant they wield and keep some enemy or rival from Obtaining the Descendant they wield.","Gift":"Quick","Gift_Description":"The Triangle Geometry makes people who are witty, quicker thinkers. They add +1 Success Level to any Action where rapid thinking may be a helpful factor.","Suggested_Personality":11,"Harmonic":[1,3,6,10],"Dissonant":[4,5,7,8]},
{"Name":"Square","Geometry":4,"Geometry_Description":"Square Characters are dependable, trustworthy and hard-working, but can be rigid and narrow-minded.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> when you are productive, helpful, or conservative.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by building, acting rigid, or bossy.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by complaining, thinking literally or working hard.","Goal":"Social","Goal_Description":"Square characters are social in nature and prefer social goals. Goals like making many friends, being a good member of society, helping those in need, supporting the local community. Such goals can often easily accommodate group goals and can the goals of friends.","Gift":"Stability","Gift_Description":"The Square Geometry makes people more stable. They add +1 Success Level to any Action where Stability (physical dexterity, or mental\/financial stability) may be a factor.","Suggested_Personality":3,"Harmonic":[1,2,4,9],"Dissonant":[3,5,7,11]},
{"Name":"Pentagon","Geometry":5,"Geometry_Description":"Pentagon Characters are the freedom-loving risk-takers, they may be fearless, or foolish.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by acting brave, reckless, or by having fun.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting rebellious, trying to effect change, or emotional.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting resilient, flexible or foolish.","Goal":"Story","Goal_Description":"Pentagon characters are the most likely to have goals set by Stories, they react to the opportunities that are presented to them, rather than setting their own. This usually places the Pentagon in a risk-taking position.","Gift":"Adventurous","Gift_Description":"The Pentagon Geometry are more adventurous than others. They add +1 Success Level on any Action that is risk-taking.","Suggested_Personality":5,"Harmonic":[1,5,7,10],"Dissonant":[2,4,6,8]},
{"Name":"Hexagon","Geometry":6,"Geometry_Description":"The Hexagon are as hard working and responsible as the Square, but with more wit and creativity. They tend to think on the big picture, rather than the details.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by nurturing others (which may be seen as meddling and include giving them Chi, or making food), or being supportive, or by dealing with the big-picture.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting sensible, responsible, or self-important.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting romantic, sensual, or self-indulgent.","Goal":"Grand","Goal_Description":"Hexagon characters are most likely to set themselves huge, ambitious goals. They are the characters most likely to decide to change the world to fit their vision of the future.","Gift":"Vision","Gift_Description":"The Hexagon Character is often a visionary, this might mean they see actual visions, or that they have a very developed imagination. They add +1 Success Level to any action to do with perception, prophecy or visual arts.","Suggested_Personality":23,"Harmonic":[3,4,6,12],"Dissonant":[5,7,10,11]},
{"Name":"Heptagon","Geometry":7,"Geometry_Description":"The Heptagon (sometimes Septagon) Character is the intellectual, but intuitive, deep &mdash; to the point of over &mdash; thinker. They can be wise, but may become aloof.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by making guesses (positing theories) or plans, asking questions, and analysing things.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by changing your mind, being proved right, or being pessimistic.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by being intuitive, being proved wrong, or acting aloof.","Goal":"Deep","Goal_Description":"Heptagon Characters are the most likely to have deep, hidden goals that they will not share with others. These goals usually relate to the deeper meaning of the Character&#39;s life, and often express as an educational, spiritual, charitable or artistic pursuit. They will often appear to align with others because it suits their Deep goal, only to turn on them later when their goals no longer align.","Gift":"Wisdom","Gift_Description":"The Heptagon Geometry makes people wise, they are deep thinkers, philosophical, knowledgeable, but intuitive and spiritual as well. They add +1 Success Level to any Action where wisdom, knowledge, or raw intellect may be a factor.","Suggested_Personality":15,"Harmonic":[3,5,7,11],"Dissonant":[2,4,6,8]},
{"Name":"Octagon","Geometry":8,"Geometry_Description":"Octagon Characters are powerful, ambitious, but ultimately materialistic individuals.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by acting disciplined, materialistic, or ambitious.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting rebellious, bossy, or generous.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting opinionated, relaxed, or persevering.","Goal":"Preserve","Goal_Description":"Octagon characters are usually invested in preserving the status quo, they dislike change and are invested in things they way they are at the start of a story. They may have minor personal goals, but these goals are usually purely material and will always reflect the status quo (they will want to become a rich, corrupt politician, not a poor, honest one if that is the system they are in). Octagon Characters are the most likely to set personal goals regarding safety and security as well as purely physiological needs, such as food, clothing or shelter.","Gift":"Manifestation","Gift_Description":"The Octagon Geometry makes people better at physically manifesting their dreams, this usually comes in the form of business skills. They add +1 Success Level to any Action to do with material wealth, business or direct manifestation of their ambition.","Suggested_Personality":2,"Harmonic":[1,2,4,8],"Dissonant":[3,6,9,12]},
{"Name":"Nonagon","Geometry":9,"Geometry_Description":"Nonagon Characters are deeply spiritual people, intuitive, compassionate and caring, they are natural humanitarians, and passionate fighters against injustice, especially in the status quo.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by acting generous, compassionate, or idealistic.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by arguing, acting passionate or knowledgeable.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by agreeing with another or acting Big-headed\/arrogant or submissive.","Goal":"Save","Goal_Description":"Nonagon Characters are driven to save others, this may be actual, with them developing a hero complex, a need to rescue others, or they may act to raise money for charities, volunteer for humanitarian causes. Nonagon Characters may actively work to alter the status quo where it shows injustice and creates suffering.","Gift":"Passion","Gift_Description":"The Nonagon Geometry drives people crazy with their passions. While they are passionate about a subject they can achieve great things, but passions usually fade after a few days, months or years, only a few are for life. They add +1 Success Level to any Action they are passionate about, but each time risk losing that Passion, if they fail the Action they must make a Passion (Psychology) Test, or persuade the Ref to let them keep it.","Suggested_Personality":18,"Harmonic":[3,4,6,9],"Dissonant":[5,7,8,10]},
{"Name":"Decagon","Geometry":10,"Geometry_Description":"Decagon Characters are like Circle Characters turned up to, well 10. They are more independent than Circles, but also work better with others.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> when you act alone, or for the good of others.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting responsible, sincere or dogmatic.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting loyal, determined, or intolerant.","Goal":"Impossible","Goal_Description":"Decagon Characters seek goals that are probably impossible, but that they can fail at over and over again, each time getting closer to their eventual goal. These Goals are often set by the Character&#39;s Personality (exactly like a Circle character), but are amplified in this context to be unachievable (at least at first). For example, a Nonagon Idol could choose to charm everyone they ever meet, or try to charm the whole world at once with some great performance.","Gift":"Resolve","Gift_Description":"The Decagon Geometry makes people determined to the point of working themselves to the bone to achieve their goals. They add +2 Success Levels to any Action but take a Flesh Wound for that resolve.","Suggested_Personality":19,"Harmonic":[1,2,5,10],"Dissonant":[3,4,6,12]},
{"Name":"Undecagon","Geometry":11,"Geometry_Description":"Undecagon Characters are mystically amplified Half-Moon Characters (they are a 2 turned up to 11!). Undecagon Characters can be so intuitive as to even believe themselves Psychic.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> by co-operating with others or being patient, knowledgeable, or vague.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting sensitive, two-faced, or mystical.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting psychic, immature or altruistic.","Goal":"Secret","Goal_Description":"Undecagon characters are the most likely to set themselves secret goals that they will not reveal. Secret goals are usually based on secrets that the character is privy to, that they may later reveal to another character, if it suits their secret goal. Classic examples include trying to find out their real identity (revealing they are not who they have claimed to be) or they may be doing anything that they can to find love, but don&#39;t want anyone to know that. ","Gift":"Psychic","Gift_Description":"The Undecagon Geometry is so about intuition, and so in tune with the world around them, that it makes people seem psychic. They add +1 Success Level on any Action where they might be able to claim Psychic assistance, resonance or similar.","Suggested_Personality":14,"Harmonic":[5,7,9,13],"Dissonant":[4,6,8,10]},
{"Name":"Dodecagon","Geometry":12,"Geometry_Description":"Dodecagon Characters are something of an intersection of circles, half-moons and triangles, they are gifted communicators and creative types, but with strong social ties that off-set rugged independence.","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> when another nearby gains Chi, you are the centre of the action, act cooperatively, or ask for help.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting courageous, talkative, methodical or tolerant","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting positive, creative, lazy or independent","Goal":"Blended","Goal_Description":"The Dodecagon character is the only Character to have blended goals. They may set a personal goal based on their Personality or Core, but this will become modified by the goals of the group they are in. Conversely, the goals of the group while worked towards by the Dodecagon character, will also often be adjusted by their personal goals.","Gift":"Communication","Gift_Description":"The Dodecagon Geometry makes characters extremely communicative. In fact, they may add +1 Success Levels to any attempt to communicate with another character, this weirdly rises to + 2 Success Levels if the Dodecagon and the target do not share a language.","Suggested_Personality":9,"Harmonic":[2,3,4,6],"Dissonant":[5,7,8,11]},
{"Name":"Triskaidecagon","Geometry":13,"Geometry_Description":"Triskaidecagon Characters are a sort of dark reflection of the stability and social nature of the Square. ","Chi":"<strong>Gain Chi <\/strong> when you are focused, pragmatic, or evasive.","Yang":"<strong>Gain Yang <\/strong> by acting independent, assured, or determined.","Yin":"<strong>Gain Yin <\/strong> by acting diligent, pedantic or by complaining.","Goal":"Complex","Goal_Description":"Triskaidecagon characters set themselves long and complex goals that have many steps and many contingencies. Their plans always assume luck will be factor (usually working against them) and they break huge goals down into smaller manageable tasks, and they are often focused on achieving the next step in their complex grand plan. Triskaidecagons can appear capricious or mercurial as their goals seem to shift and change as the steps unfold, but know that there is always a much greater plan in motion in the Triskaidecagon character&#39;s head.","Gift":"Luck","Gift_Description":"The Triskaidecagon Geometry makes people have extreme luck. Sadly you can never tell if the luck will be good or bad. On any Action they may roll a 1d6 Luck dice. <div class=\"t13ne-tablewrap\"><table class=\"t13ne-table\"><thead><tr><th>Roll<\/th><th>Result<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>1<\/td><td>-2 Success Levels<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>2-3<\/td><td>-1 Success Level<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>4-5<\/td><td>+1 Success Level<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>6<\/td><td>+2 Success Levels<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/div>","Suggested_Personality":6,"Harmonic":[3,7,11,13],"Dissonant":[1,4,5,9]}];

